            <div class="text" style="margin:10px 6vw 30px 6vw;">
                <h>About missingchip.com</h>
                <p>This website is hosted on a Raspberry Pi in my Binghamton dorm room. It runs Raspbian Lite as an Apache web server. All the HTML and CSS is made by me, from scratch. I purchased the domain through hover, and their DNS server is pointed via a CNAME record to a dynamic DNS solution provided by No-IP. The website is updated through some scripts I wrote for myself. All of the resources for the website are <a href="https://github.com/MissingChip/missingchip.com">on GitHub</a>. I made this website to experiment with networking and web design, and because I wanted a website to showcase my work. Is this the most efficient and easy way to have a personal website? Absolutely not. It is, however, much more fun and educational than less exploration-heavy alternatives.</p>
